        <\/div>\n    <\/article><article class=\"eael-grid-post eael-post-grid-column\" data-id=\"7643\">\n        <div class=\"eael-grid-post-holder\">\n            <div class=\"eael-grid-post-holder-inner\"><div class=\"eael-entry-wrapper\"><header class=\"eael-entry-header\"><h2 class=\"eael-entry-title\"><a\n                        class=\"eael-grid-post-link\"\n                        href=\"https:\/\/diegovz.com\/blog\/memoria-en-el-ux\"\n                        title=\"Memoria en el UX\">Memoria en el UX<\/a><\/h2><\/header><div class=\"eael-entry-content\">\n                        <div class=\"eael-grid-post-excerpt\"><p>En este art\u00edculo analizaremos los diferentes tipos de memoria que tenemos las personas y c\u00f3mo dise\u00f1ar atendiendo a cada una de ellas.<\/p><a\n                            href=\"https:\/\/diegovz.com\/blog\/memoria-en-el-ux\"\n                            class=\"eael-post-elements-readmore-btn\">Leer m\u00e1s<\/a><\/div>\n                    <\/div><div class=\"eael-entry-footer\"><div class=\"eael-entry-meta\"><span class=\"eael-posted-on\"><time datetime=\"June 9, 2021\">June 9, 2021<\/time><\/span><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div>\n        <\/div>\n    <\/article><article class=\"eael-grid-post eael-post-grid-column\" data-id=\"7746\">\n        <div class=\"eael-grid-post-holder\">\n            <div class=\"eael-grid-post-holder-inner\"><div class=\"eael-entry-wrapper\"><header class=\"eael-entry-header\"><h2 class=\"eael-entry-title\"><a\n                        class=\"eael-grid-post-link\"\n                        href=\"https:\/\/diegovz.com\/en\/blog\/memory-in-ux\"\n                        title=\"Memory in UX\">Memory in UX<\/a><\/h2><\/header><div class=\"eael-entry-content\">\n                        <div class=\"eael-grid-post-excerpt\"><p>In this article we will analyze the different types of memory that people have and how to design for each of them.<\/p><a\n                            href=\"https:\/\/diegovz.com\/e