\">\n            <div class=\"eael-grid-post-holder-inner\"><div class=\"eael-entry-wrapper\"><header class=\"eael-entry-header\"><h2 class=\"eael-entry-title\"><a\n                        class=\"eael-grid-post-link\"\n                        href=\"https:\/\/diegovz.com\/en\/blog\/hicks-law\"\n                        title=\"Hick&#8217;s law\">Hick&#8217;s law<\/a><\/h2><\/header><div class=\"eael-entry-content\">\n                        <div class=\"eael-grid-post-excerpt\"><p>Hick's Law states that the time required to make a decision is increased by the number of options available.<\/p><a\n                            href=\"https:\/\/diegovz.com\/en\/blog\/hicks-law\"\n                            class=\"eael-post-elements-readmore-btn\">Leer m\u00e1s<\/a><\/div>\n                    <\/div><div class=\"eael-entry-footer\"><div class=\"eael-entry-meta\"><span class=\"eael-posted-on\"><time datetime=\"May 24, 2021\">May 24, 2021<\/time><\/span><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div>\n        <\/div>\n    <\/article><article class=\"eael-grid-post eael-post-grid-column\" data-id=\"5751\">\n        <div class=\"eael-grid-post-holder\">\n            <div class=\"eael-grid-post-holder-inner\"><div class=\"eael-entry-wrapper\"><header class=\"eael-entry-header\"><h2 class=\"eael-entry-title\"><a\n                        class=\"eael-grid-post-link\"\n                        href=\"https:\/\/diegovz.com\/en\/blog\/mental-models-in-ux\"\n                        title=\"Mental models in UX\">Mental models in UX<\/a><\/h2><\/header><div class=\"eael-entry-content\">\n                        <div class=\"eael-grid-post-excerpt\"><p>Mental models play an important role in Human-Computer Interaction (HCI) and Interaction Design. They relate to the way a user perceives the world around them and are based on beliefs.<\/p><a\n                            href=\"https:\/\/diegovz.com\/en\/blog\/mental-models-in-ux\"\n                            class=\"eael-post-elements-readmore-btn\">Le